"Turchetto M., Vanin S.","Forensic entomology and climatic change",2004,"Forensic Science International","146","SUPPL.",,"S207","S209",,,10.1016/j.forsciint.2004.09.064,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-11844285675&partnerID=40&md5=82ce8f2239387f4f269fae3b26f0d449","Dipartimento di Biologia, Università di Padova, Via U. Bassi 58/B, 35131 Padova, I., Italy","Turchetto, M., Dipartimento di Biologia, Università di Padova, Via U. Bassi 58/B, 35131 Padova, I., Italy; Vanin, S., Dipartimento di Biologia, Università di Padova, Via U. Bassi 58/B, 35131 Padova, I., Italy","Forensic entomology establishes the postmortem interval (PMI) by studying cadaveric fauna. The PMI today is still largely based on tables of insect succession on human cadavers compiled in the late 19th- or mid-20th centuries. In the last few years, however, the gradual warming of the climate has been changing faunal communities by favouring the presence of thermophilous species. To demonstrate how globalisation and climate change are overcoming geographic barriers, we present some cases of southern and allochthonous species found in north-east Italy during our entomo-forensic investigations. © 2004 Elsevier Ireland Ltd. All rights reserved.","Arthropods; Forensic entomology; Global warming; Postmortem interval (PMI)","article; cadaver; climate change; fauna; forensic science; geography; global climate; human; Italy; priority journal; thermophilic bacterium; warming; zoology; Animals; Climate; Diptera; Entomology; Forensic Anthropology; Humans; Italy",,,,,,"Mégnin, P., La faune de cadavres. Application de l'entomologie a la médicine légale (1894) Encyclopedie Scientifique des Aides-Memoirés, , Marson, Paris, Gauthier-Villars, Paris; Jonston, W., Villeneuve, G., On the medico-legal application of entomology (1897) Montreal Med. J., 26, pp. 81-90; (2001) Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis, , IPCC 2001 Cambridge University Press; Venturi, F., Notulae dipterologicae X Specie nuove per l'Italia (1956) Boll. Soc. Entomol. Italy, 34, p. 56; Turchetto, M., Implicazioni entomologico-forensi dell'introduzione in Italia della mosca neotropicale Hermetia illucens L. (Diptera: Stratiomyidae) (2000) Rivista Italiana di Medicina Legale, 22, pp. 1279-1290; Turchetto, M., Lafisca, S., Costantini, G., Postmortem interval (PMI) determined by study sarcophagous biocenosis: Three cases from the Province of Venice (Italy) (2001) Forensic Sci. Int., 120, pp. 28-31; Turchetto, M., Vanin, S., Forensic evaluations on a crime case with monospecific necrophagous fly population infected by two parasitoid species (2004) Aggrawal's Internet J. Forensic Med. Toxicol., 5, pp. 12-18; Thomas, C.D., Bodsworth, E.J., Wilson, R.J., Simmons, A.D., Davies, Z.G., Musche, M., Konradt, L., Ecological and evolutionary processes at expanding range margins (2001) Nature, 411, pp. 577-581; Hill, J.K., Thomas, C.D., Fox, R., Telfer, M.G., Willis, S.G., Hasher, J., Huntley, B., Responses of butterflies to twentieth century climate warming: Implications for future ranges (2002) Proc. R. Soc. Lond. B, 269, pp. 2163-2171","Dipartimento di Biologia, Università di Padova, Via U. Bassi 58/B, 35131 Padova, I.Italy; email: margherita.turchetto@unipd.it",,,,,,,,03790738,,FSIND,15639577,"English","Forensic Sci. Int.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-11844285675
